<item>
            <title>[FLINK-14145] getLatestCheckpoint(true) returns wrong checkpoint</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-14145</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The flag to prefer checkpoints for recovery introduced in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-11159&quot; title=&quot;Allow configuration whether to fall back to savepoints for restore&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-11159&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-11159&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; returns the wrong checkpoint if:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;checkpoints are preferred  (&lt;tt&gt;getLatestCheckpoint(true)&lt;/tt&gt;),&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;the latest checkpoint is &lt;b&gt;not&lt;/b&gt; a savepoint,&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;more than a single checkpoint is retained.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;The current implementation assumes that the latest checkpoint is a savepoint and skips over it. I attached a patch for &lt;tt&gt;StandaloneCompletedCheckpointStoreTest&lt;/tt&gt; that demonstrates the issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You can apply the patch via &lt;tt&gt;git am -3 &amp;lt; *.patch&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
